#Messages		;! 203 total


$Name: Welcome Message
$Message: Good morning pilot.  Don't touch the controls until told to do so.
+Wave Name: BTM1_01.wav

$Name: Target
$Message: The first function you will learn is targeting. [Press $t$] Target me.
+Wave Name: BTM1_02.wav

$Name: Target box
$Message: In the lower left hand corner of your HUD is your Target View.  The top line displays the targeted ship's name and class.
+Wave Name: BTM1_03.wav

$Name: Target box 2
$Message: The next line shows the distance to your target and its speed.
+Wave Name: BTM1_04.wav

$Name: Off Screen Indicator
$Message: Note the brackets around my ship indicating I am your current target.
+Wave Name: BTM1_05.wav

$Name: Off screen indicator 2
$Message: As I fly out of view, the offscreen indicator will display.  It points in the direction you must turn in order to face your target.
+Wave Name: BTM1_06.wav

$Name: Radar
$Message: The circular gauge near the bottom of your HUD is the radar.  Friendly ships are shown in green.  Hostile ships appear as red.
+Wave Name: BTM1_07.wav

$Name: Face Instructor
$Message: Using your main flight controller turn your ship toward mine.  Stop when my ship is in your center reticle.
+Wave Name: BTM1_08.wav

$Name: Good
$Message: Good.  Now stay in that position.
+Wave Name: BTM1_09.wav

$Name: Facing Instructor 3
$Message: Now turn toward my ship again.
+Wave Name: BTM1_10.wav

$Name: Match Speed
$Message: [Press $m$] Match my speed.
+Wave Name: BTM1_11.wav

$Name: Match Speed Now
$Message: Match my speed now.
+Wave Name: BTM1_12.wav

$Name: Speed Gauge
$Message: To the left of the reticle is the speed gauge.  The capital M next to the current speed indicates that you are matching speed with your target.
+Wave Name: BTM1_13.wav

$Name: Acceleration
$Message: Now I want you to use your acceleration key, [$a$] to move to within 75 units of me.  Do not collide with my ship.
+Wave Name: BTM1_14.wav

$Name: Deceleration
$Message: Good.  Now decelerate [$z$] to drop 200 units behind me.
+Wave Name: BTM1_15.wav

$Name: Afterburner
$Message: Good.  Now the afterburner.  [$tab$]  Engage your afterburner.
+Wave Name: BTM1_16.wav

$Name: Max Speed
$Message: That extra speed is useful for quick evasive maneuvers.  Maintain your max top speed. [$\$].  Try it now.
+Wave Name: BTM1_17.wav

$Name: Full Stop
$Message: Now come to a complete stop. [$backspace$]
+Wave Name: BTM1_18.wav

$Name: Drone Warp In
$Message: Drone 01 has just warped in.  Target it. [Press $t$].
+Wave Name: BTM1_19.wav

$Name: Target Cargo
$Message: A group of cargo containers has just warped in.  Target C-01a. [Press $t$]
+Wave Name: BTM1_20.wav

$Name: Inspecting
$Message: Good.  Now inspect these cargo containers.
+Wave Name: BTM1_21.wav

$Name: Destroy Cargo
$Message: The sound you heard indicates the cargo container has been inspected.  Notice the cargo display in the target box at your lower left.
+Wave Name: BTM1_22.wav

$Name: Destroy Cargo 2
$Message: Near the center of your HUD the hull integrity of your target is displayed.  Notice that it has dropped from 100%.
+Wave Name: BTM1_23.wav

$Name: Destroy Cargo 3
$Message: Now Destroy C-01a.
+Wave Name: BTM1_24.wav

$Name: Kill Rest of Cargo
$Message: Good.  Now destroy C-02b and C-03a.  Remember to target them [$t$].
+Wave Name: BTM1_25.wav

$Name: Kill New Cargo
$Message: Let's see how quickly you can destroy these new cargo containers.  Target them [$t$] and destroy them with your ML-16.
+Wave Name: BTM1_26.wav

$Name: Warp Out
$Message: Good job.  Now it's time to leave.  [Press $alt-j$]
+Wave Name: BTM1_27.wav

$Name: Off Screen Indicator 3
$Message: Note how it moves as I fly around.  It is always pointing at your target.
+Wave Name: BTM1_28.wav

$Name: Off Screen Indicator 4
$Message: Notice how the triangles separate.  The farther apart they are, the farther you'll have to turn to face your target.
+Wave Name: BTM1_29.wav

$Name: Off Screne Indicator 5
$Message: Finally, note the number by the indicator.  This is the distance to your target.
+Wave Name: BTM1_30.wav

$Name: Match Speed 1 1/2
$Message: Good.  Now follow me.  Note how your speed automatically changes to match mine.
+Wave Name: BTM1_31.wav

$Name: Afterburner 2
$Message: The gauge to the left of your speed gauge indicates remaining afterburner power.  Note that it is consumed rapidly.
+Wave Name: BTM1_32.wav

$Name: Drone 2
$Message: Good.  Now fly within 100 units of it, then come to a stop.  [$backspace$]  Be careful not to fly too fast.
+Wave Name: BTM1_33.wav

$Name: Drone 3
$Message: Well done.  Note that it takes some time to come to a complete stop.
+Wave Name: BTM1_34.wav

$Name: Inspect 2
$Message: In order to determine the contents of a ship or cargo container, you must target it, face it, and fly within 150 units.
+Wave Name: BTM1_35.wav

$Name: Destroy Cargo 1 1/2
$Message: Now, fire your primary weapon [press $left ctrl$] at C-01a.  Hit it a few times, but do not destroy it.
+Wave Name: BTM1_36.wav

$Name: Destroy Cargo 2 1/2
$Message: This information is also available in the upper right of your target display.
+Wave Name: BTM1_37.wav

$Name: Kill Rest of Cargo 2
$Message: Good job.
+Wave Name: BTM1_38.wav

$Name: End Mission
$Message: Inability to follow instructions results in immediate failure.  Jump back to base to reschedule training Phase 1.  [Press $alt-j$]
+Wave Name: BTM1_39.wav

